Paper: hep-th/0002037

Date: 2000-02-04

Title: Stability and BPS branes

Authors: Michael R. Douglas, Bartomeu Fiol and Christian R\"omelsberger

Comments: harvmac, 18 pp

We define the concept of Pi-stability, a generalization of mu-stability ofvector bundles, and argue that it characterizes N=1 supersymmetric braneconfigurations and BPS states in very general string theory compactificationswith N=2 supersymmetry in four dimensions.